
@startuml

' Define classes
class City {
    - name: String
    - inhabitants: int
}

class Attraction {
    - name: String
    - address: String
}

class GuidedTour {
    - duration: int  // e.g., in hours
    - tourNumber: int
    - maxVisitors: int = 20
}

class Visitor {
    - name: String
}

class Guide {
    - name: String
}

class Discount {
    - amount: float
}

' Relationships
City "1" -- "many" Attraction : has
Attraction "1" -- "many" GuidedTour : offers
GuidedTour "1" -- "many" Visitor : includes (max 20)
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires
Visitor "1" -- "many" Discount : may have
Guide "1" -- "many" Discount : may offer

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **City** has multiple **Attractions**.
- Each **Attraction** can have multiple **GuidedTours**.
- A **GuidedTour** can include up to 20 **Visitors**.
- Each **GuidedTour** must be led by a **Guide**.
- A **Visitor** may have a **Discount** for a specific tour.
- A **Guide** may also offer discounts.

